tyle=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td></tr><tr align=\"center\"></tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Roose_Ryswell&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Hosteen</b>: We should take the fight to <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis</a> and make an end to him.<br />\n</p><p><b>Harwood</b>: Leave <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">the castle</a>? Would you have us charge blindly into the snow?\n</p>\n<b>Roose</b>: To fight Lord Stannis we would first need to find him. Our scouts go out the <a href=\"/index.php/Hunter%27s_Gate\" title=\"Hunter&#39;s Gate\">Hunter's Gate</a>, but of late, none of them return.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Hosteen_Frey\" title=\"Hosteen Frey\">Hosteen Frey</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Harwood_Stout\" title=\"Harwood Stout\">Harwood Stout</a>, and Roose</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Roose_Ryswell&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The appendices of <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Appendix\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Appendix\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> and <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Appendix\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Appendix\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> list <a href=\"/index.php/Roger_Ryswell\" title=\"Roger Ryswell\">Roger</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Rickard_Ryswell\" title=\"Rickard Ryswell\">Rickard</a>, and Roose as Rodrik's quarrelsome cousins, but the text of <i>A Dance with Dragons</i> specifies them as his sons in <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_20\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 20\">20. Reek II</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_32\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 32\">32. Reek III</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_32\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 32\">Chapter 32</a>, Reek III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></